description:
“Create Together was a really great experience/event. The live streams were a lot of fun to watch and be a part of. During the month I learned a lot about how valuable and insightful collaborations can be. I was motivated to join the event by how much I enjoyed listening to the create together vol. 1 EP and watching the artist livestream from last year.” - Sam Day

“I Wonder” is the result of a super fun collaboration with my friends Hendrik and Sam. We have known each other for about a year now and spent nearly every day on discord since quarantine began. Everyone shared their ideas and visions in the chat and it was so nice to see all these songs slowly come to life. I found most of my inspiration in my current music taste and also songs from Hendrik and Sam, but also the livestreams, which showed me new ways and methods to make new sounds.” - Dust of Apollon

“This is going to sound cheesy, and I’m getting emotional writing this, but honestly we found inspiration from one another. Just the beautiful synergy we all had throughout the whole process was a thing of beauty. I love my friends so much.” - Hendrik Joerges

🌎 Presave create together vol. 2

description:
🎮 OUT NOW 🎮 EoL.lnk.to/TheNextLevelEP

In a matter of just a few years, D-Sturb transformed from a promising newcomer to a key artist in Hardstyle. Countless hours of hard work in the studio and bringing daring creative ideas to life were the driving forces behind his success, as this humble artist quickly became a favourite among many. 

Throughout his intricate six-part live-act 'The Next Level,' D-Sturb shares was able to share the story behind his career journey so far, with each level representing a different phase of his career. The first of the six levels began at Supremacy 2018, and the final level was played out last weekend at Intents Festival on the colossal mainstage. Each level is defined by a special 'challenge', in which D-Sturb had to complete a track that symbolised a specific phase of his career.
Tracklist:
1. E-Force & Frequencerz - Attention (D-Sturb The Next Level Remix)
2. D-Sturb - Until It's Gone (The Next Level Remix)
3. Warface & Frequencerz - Menace (D-Sturb The Next Level Remix)
4. D-Sturb - High Power (The Next Level Remix)
5. D-Sturb - Apocalyptic Darkness (The Next Level Remix)

D-Sturb - The Next Level EP [EOL097] is OUT NOW on End of Line Recordings.

description:
Roller Coaster is a track with two versions, a bounce and a trance one, both of them sharing common elements but going in different directions.

Common elements include the rhythmic base (inspired, in part, by the Speed Garage), bass and drop. But above all what they share is that the some main sounds go up and down constantly, giving the feeling of being in an amusement park, hence its name.

Instead, the two versions convey different sensations. While the bounce is more upbeat, playful and bouncy the trance one is a little bit more serious and includes a melody. 

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Roller Coaster es un tema con dos versiones, una bounce y otra trance, cada uno de ellos compartiendo elementos comunes pero dirigiéndose en direcciones diferentes. 

Los elementos comunes incluyen la base rítmica (inspirada, en parte, en Speed Garage), el bajo y el drop. Pero sobre todo lo que comparten es que algunos sonidos principales suben y bajan constantemente, dando la sensación de estar en un parque de atracciones, de ahí su nombre.

En cambio, las versiones transmiten sensaciones diferentes. Mientras que la bounce es más alegre, juguetón y saltarín la trance es algo más seria e incluye una melodía.

description:
Plastician Presents - Wavepool 2
Terrorhythm Redordings
TERR055

18 months on from the now legendary DJ mix "The Wave Pool MMXV", Plastician presents the much anticipated follow up mix, this time with an accompanying 29 track album of the tracks included within.

The question asked of the first mix was whether or not a new sound was emerging out of the internet - 18 months on, and countless great productions since, this collection of tracks from some of the Wave movement's key players and new blood seeks to gain approval of the Wave genre's arrival.

Including tracks from Klimeks, Kareful, Skit, Sorsari, Deadcrow, Anubis XIII, Hnrk, Noah B, Brothel and more - it's clear to see that this compilation has called upon some of the scene's most noted producers to stake it's claim.

Mixed and curated by Plastician whose Rinse FM radio show was the platform for this movement to be brought to the attention of the wider public, as well as his Survey parties in Phonox being the initial club night at which this scene established itself outside of the internet - this album is another statement from the man that this sound is not trying to disappear into obscurity any time soon.
title: Meteo (out now via Terrorhythm)

description:
A fun EP that I was working on for a quite a while and I am glad that it is finally done. The EP features 3 tracks, two of which are a slightly more modern sounding version of what I like about older style hardcore. Disappear was a fun one, I took some vocal samples I remember hearing back when I first started making music, and made a whole track around them. It was really neat to be able to take something from my past and make something out of it I could only dream of back then.

Don't Say You Love Me uses some vocals that I first heard in a Ryuno track. I was browsing some sample packs and stumbled across the vocals, so I just had to make my own track using them. I had actually been sitting on this track for a while, but was not sure how to release it. Lucky I released it here, because if I had released it when I wanted to, it would have not been as good, it still needed a fair amount of work.

Lullaby is a 200bpm happy hardcore type track. This was my first time making something at this tempo, and it was a lot of fun. I was listening to a lot of Kobaryo and faster j-core in general, and that inspired me to make Lullaby. I don't think I fully captured the sound, but that is okay, because I still think I made a cool track.

The EP also features an illustration by myself and I am happy with how it came out. I used to draw a lot back in the day, but I stopped once I started getting heavily into making music. I decided a while back to casually get back into and bought a nice tablet for it. It took some getting used to moving to digital, but I am glad I did, makes things way easier. It is really refreshing to have one of my illustrations as the art for my music. 

This was released early on my Patreon. If you like what I do and want to help support me, as well as get access to early releases and other goodies, please consider supporting me on Patreon.

Check out my Patreon here: https://www.patreon.com/audiovitamin

GET IT HERE: https://audiovitamin.bandcamp.com/album/disappear

description:
This year's Stereo Homicide EP. I was originally going to go for the same sort of sound that I went for with the last two, by using all the same sounds again. However, I quickly found out that I was pretty bored with that sound and did not want to tread the same ground again. So with this one I set out to update the Stereo Homicide sound a little bit, while still retaining a similar feeling. I am pretty happy with what I was able to come up with and I feel I made another cool Halloween EP. My brother did the illustration again this year, big thanks to him for that :) 

The first song is called "The Old Ways", it is the first thing I started for this project and uses all the same sounds from the last two EPs. Despite it using all the old sounds, I am still really happy with it, I just knew I could not do that for another three tracks. It is called "The Old Ways" because it uses the old sound set, but I also was imagining the old traditions of a murder cult while writing this track. It also kind of ties into the cover art. The last two releases featured knives, while this one uses a gun, so knives being the old ways.

"A New Monster" is probably the most modern sounding track on the EP. I went for a neuro style bass and tried to give it a more up to date sound, while still using old breaks and the Stereo Homicide sound set. I went for the title "A New Monster" because it has a more modern sound and I imagined a new member of the murder cult giving in to their psychotic desires. I was also imagining them using a gun, rather than knives like the rest of the members, which is something the other cult members don't approve of. 

"The Sickness" is my attempt to make a song that is sort of a hybrid between Big Beat and DnB. I think I managed to pull it off for the most part, I wanted some acid parts in the track, but could not make them fit. "The Sickness" refers to the psychosis that is taking over the new cult member. They have already given into it, but they are still fighting it to some degree.

Finally, "Where Is The Rain" is a more chilled out, minimal DnB track that I made because I was really inspired by the song at the end of a Alex Ball YouTube video. I ended up making something that is not too similar, but that is probably a good thing and I am still really happy with what I made. This song is about the character fully snapping, killing all the other cult members and then having immense regret for all the people they have killed and the monster they have become. They are wondering where is the rain that will wash away all that they have done and what they have become.

Happy Halloween everyone!

This was released early on my Patreon. If you like what I do and want to help support me, as well as get access to early releases and other goodies, please consider supporting me on Patreon.

Check out my Patreon here: https://www.patreon.com/audiovitamin

description:
I have been interested in making future bass/kawaii bass for a while now and I finally have a collection of tracks ready for you in that genre. Since it is a new genre for me, I thought I should make a new alias for it. When I was trying to think of an alias for Mana Weaver, Magic Splash was one of the names I came up with, but felt it was too cute and lighthearted for the the sound I go for with Mana Weaver. I think it is perfect for future bass though! The name almost perfectly fits the mood I am going for, and is just versatile enough that the sound doesn't have to be too narrow to fit it thematically.

The EP is three tracks long, and they are each a little different in sound, while staying on theme. "Afternoon Video Games" is the most kawaii sounding of the three and is more traditional in style. "Daydreamer" is actually an older song that I made in 2016, but never officially released until now, it was originally under my Nakura alias. This one is less kawaii sounding, and has a more regular future bass feel. Lastly, "High Score" has a more traditional style beat, and focuses more heavily on the chiptune elements than the other tracks. I am really happy with all three tracks and am proud of this EP.

The artwork is by the awesome Lexeria, you can check them out on their Twitter: https://twitter.com/Lexeria001

This was released early on my Patreon. If you like what I do and want to help support me, as well as get access to early releases and other goodies, please consider supporting me on Patreon.

description:
J. Kong is back for his 4th EP outing on In:flux Audio, delivering two original tracks that showcase his talent as a producer within the 140 scene. Title track 'Santana' sees him arcing back to his early grime sounds as he teams up with the talented Charlie Dax on vocals, the pair complimenting each other to create a right earworm of a track to kick off the EP. The B-side to the release, 'Delight', sees J. Kong bringing more of his recent production vibes to the EP - a much more stripped back affair that showcases the producers love for sound design and keeping the listener engaged throughout. Stellar work!

On remix duty we bring through man like Dunman to tackle 'Delight'. The producer has been on absolute fire this past year, and here is no exception, as he takes the track and flips it into UK Garage hybrid, with the smoothest intro you'll hear this year before the 2nd drop breaks out in the best way possible.

===========================================================================

02. J. Kong - Delight (Original Mix)
03. J. Kong - Delight (Dunman Remix)

description:
1point5 is back for his first solo EP on In:flux Audio since 'Perception' back in January 2015. He has been pottering around the label plenty since then though, with plenty of remixes and of course, his collab EP last November with founders Tik&Borrow. This time round we showcase three tracks from the producer, all of which showcase his evolution into firmer Dubstep territory, whilst retaining that signature 2-step 1point5 sound that we know and love.

On remixes, it's a selection of label loves who are returning the favour to 1point5 after he provided superb remixes on their EPs. Ali McK & IYZ are up first, with their reworking of 'Backspace' - a more twinkly affair with a superb reworking of the lead section into something more dark and brooding, whilst still retaining the duos ear for a banger. Fork and Knife closes out the EP with his UK Garage take on the lead track 'Solar Signal', all percussion, wubs and vibes - the perfect exit to a stunning EP.

===========================================================================

Tracklisting:
01. 1point5 - Solar Signal (Original Mix)
02. 1point5 - Backspace (Original Mix)
03. 1point5 - Cassini (Original Mix)
04. 1point5 - Backspace (Ali McK & IYZ Remix)
05. 1point5 - Solar Signal (Fork and Knife Remix)

===========================================================================

Check Out Ali McK here --> @alimck

description:
Label founders Tik&Borrow are back for their first EP of 2021 on In:flux Audio, coming in heavy with two original tracks for their latest EP 'Erebus & Terror'. The duo have been honing their intricate dubstep stylings since their last solo outing on the label in May 2020, and on the way to this EP they've had releases on Dirty Beats, Simply Deep, SND SYSTM CLTR and Frozen Plates to name a few. This EP sees them return to the heavier side of their sound, but maintaining the progressions seen through the past year, to create something that is fresh and forward thinking.

On remixes, label newby Qwirk tackles 'Erebus', taking the original and turning it into a breaks-dubstep hybrid that had us spinning in our chair upon it landing in our inbox. Dystinkt follows suit in the blending of styles, taking a more funky-dubstep approach to his remix of 'Terror', brining us a track that has groove for days and will get any dancefloor vibing.

===========================================================================

Tracklisting:
01. Tik&Borrow - Erebus (Original Mix)
02. Tik&Borrow - Terror (Original Mix)
03. Tik&Borrow - Erebus (Qwirk Remix)
04. Tik&Borrow - Terror (Dystinkt Remix)

===========================================================================

Check Out Qwirk here --> @qwirkk

description:
Dystinkt returns to In:flux Audio for his second EP, 'Technicolour', and this one sees him levelling up the sound design work from his last EP outing 'Tripletz' with three tasty cuts that walk the line between the OG Dubstep sound and those Grimey vibes that makes his work some of our favourite within the scene.

Title track 'Technicolour' kicks the EP off in style, pulling out all the stops with some incredible Joker-esque synth work that will have you pulling screwface in the rave come June 21st. He follows the title track up with 'Dabs' which brings a wicked blend of bass progression and drumwork to the table, with 'Wonked Out' doing what it says on the tin to bring the three excellent original tracks to a close.

On remix duty we're chuffed to welcome back man like Reso to the label for the first time since 2017 plus another one of roster favourites in J. Kong, who both give lend their immense talents to remixing title track 'Technicolour'. Reso goes full 2010 on his remix, lacing the wicked synth work from the original over gnarling bass tones and punching drums. J. Kong goes in a different direction with the track, giving it a stripped back work over like only he can - a minimal take on the original that is the perfect way to close out the EP.

===========================================================================

Tracklisting:
01. Dystinkt - Technicolour (Original Mix)
02. Dystinkt - Dabs (Original Mix)
03. Dystinkt - Wonked Out (Original Mix)
04. Dystinkt - Technicolour (Reso Remix)
05. Dystinkt - Technicolour (J. Kong Remix)

===========================================================================

Check Out Dystinkt here --> @dystinktdubs
Check Out Reso here --> @reso
Check Out J. Kong here --> @jkongmusic

This track called 'Deep Into My Mind' is an uplifter with tones of melancholia. Searching deep in our minds for a true feeling of what trance brings us. Happiness, sadness, compassion is brought out with the core in the stunning melody. The break brings feelings emerged out of epic proportions and the build escalates us into the true gift of trance. Feel it deep into your mind!

For the remix we have PrajDy, another known producer from the same country as the original maker. Here we feel a more progressive vibe with deeper sounds. The wondrous piano melody in the break-part takes this remix into a different level than the original. This track now has the infusion of two excellent sounds but with same enchanting result. Facing the facts of searching deep within ourselves.

Download/Stream: https://FSOE.lnk.to/IAATMAlbum

Aly & Fila are proud to present their sixth studio artist album, 'It's All About The Melody' which will be released on Monday 25th November this year on their label Future Sound Of Egypt. Two years have passed since the trance pharaohs released their last long player, meanwhile the duo have been hard at work in the studio creating a formidable array of 15 dance records. Their vision for this stunning piece of music is as simple as the title suggests; to produce and mix melodious dance music that centers on their melody and musicality.

The album features many Aly & Fila hit singles such as the vocal sensations 'Gravity' with Deirdre McLaughlin and 'Breathe' with Chris Jones, but it also yields ingenious instrumentals like 'Te Espero Aqui' and the ultimate track 'Finally'. 'It's All About The Melody' doesn't shy away from collaborations either as Aly & Fila have teamed up with some of the most respected artists in the industry from James Dymond on their track 'Wasteland' to songstress JES for 'I Won't Let You Fall' in the incredible uplifting mix.

Aly & Fila have certainly proven their ability not only as international, world class DJs but one of the best production duos of today. Their album will be released on physical CD as well as at all digital streaming and download portals.

description:
The Late Night Soundtrack project is a collection of some of the first tracks I’ve completed as a solo act. In the 15 years since SpectraSoul formed, I’ve had very little chance to write any music on my own - let alone put a whole project together. It took me a while to find my own process and way of working. I tried to focus on developing new techniques and strategies, while also sourcing new instruments to work with. I bought an Elektron Analog 4 from @dBridge_exitrecords and that was the beginning. There are sounds from that synthesiser on every single track I’ve made since I bought it.

The concept of Late Night Soundtrack was to shine a light on the artistry that can be achieved within drum & bass, whilst also placing a focus back on the context from which the genre was born and evolved from: the club. I wanted to pair rich bass textures and punchy DJ tools like ‘Dotodotdash’ and ‘Barriers of Language’ with deeply musical cuts like ‘Cheap Love’ and ‘Fragments’, whilst also including the more leftfield excursions of ‘Setting Traps’ and ‘Overnight Express’. As a collection, these 14 tracks show the breadth of my taste within the genre - I get bored if i write the same kind of music over and over again and hate the idea of being put in a box. I wanted to set out my stall in terms of my aesthetic, intention and vision. I find myself in an internal battle at times. I want to make music that can be played in the club context but that also has a richness and musicality to it. With the Late Night Soundtrack project, I’ve tried to marry those two ideals together; tracks that are club-functional sit alongside tracks that are underpinned by more emotionally-led musicality. Sometimes I tried to achieve both in one track! In a full and finished form, this collection of music speaks to the mantra of my Must Make platform; to keep creating, to keep learning, and to keep pushing forward.
—
Workforce

description:
Next up from Sofa Sound is the forthcoming collaborations from drum & bass heavyweights DLR, Break, Randall and Ulterior Motive, a collective who’ve all helped to pioneer the genre whilst staying inherently underground. Whilst Break and Randall have laid its foundations, producers like DLR and Ulterior Motive have shaped the more contemporary scene, although both tracks signify the colossal engineering standards of each featuring artist. The established names also bring their weight to Sofa Sound’s back catalogue, which has expanded since its creation by DLR in 2017. 

DLR, Break and Randall come together for lead track ‘Song & Dance’, an old-school reminiscent roller with snipped up, mc-lead vocal samples and jazzy instrumentals. The energy between all three artists is instantly recognisable, with Randall’s old-school approach shining through each layer. On top of strung guitar notes and a hook which nods to its namesake, ‘Song & Dance’ blends a mixture of styles to present a versatile addition to Sofa Sound.

Next comes ‘Modules’, featuring a combination of sonics recorded through Ulterior Motive’s modular set up. The ruminating drums and basses brought from the collections of their collaborators deliver its funkier elements, with the bassline fluctuating between notes and twisting its way through a melodic undertow. Alongside its unusual structure, the track’s organic approach and frequent switches grab its listener unaware. Another imperative release on Sofa Sound, the imprint has shown its commitment to artists from across the spectrum, through both its digital releases and physical discography additions.

description:
Drum and Bass aficionado Halogenix has prepared his first EP under the moniker of his pseudo side project Lordel, aptly named Lordel. Liberated from any kind of artistic limitations or expectations as he introduces listeners to fresh work, Halogenix is eager to make a statement with this EP and show fans that he has plenty of stories to tell through many genres. Lordel is out via Zeds Dead’s Deadbeats imprint on November 20th. 

With a sound self-described as raw, organic, and melancholy, this EP serves as the perfect introduction to the Lordel project. Previously a founding member of Ivy Lab, Halogenix demonstrates his skills as a producer across all 6 tracks, masterfully weaving through hip hop, downtempo, and lo-fi beats. Filled with sonic synths, creeping melodies, and invasive percussion, Halogenix is opening the door to yet another memorable chapter in his long and diverse career. 

Tracklist:
Purpan
Chipset
Wolf
Bollo
Ennui
Philly To Pittsburgh

Halogenix’s career began with the inspiration he drew from his father, a French horn player in the London Symphony Orchestra who had the opportunity to be a part of the soundtracks for Star Wars and Raiders of the Lost Ark. While his prolific career has been filled to the brim with unique experiences, releases, and collaborations, such as works with Noisia and SHADES, remixes for BANKS and The Glitch Mob, and production credits with Foreign Beggars, Roses Gabor and hotly tipped UK rapper Benny Mails, he’s more than ready to begin anew with his Lordel project.

For All Press Inquiries:
info@davidkim.biz

description:
https://drumcode.ffm.to/dc247

Produced off the back of a profoundly inspiring trip to his homeland last year, Luigi Madonna crafts the pin-sharp ‘Italian Shocks’ EP. The Amsterdam-based artist is a key Drumcode contributor, who runs the label off the back of last year’s well-received collaborative EP ‘Mad World’ with Roberto Capuano. 

The title track is brain-spangling, industrial and brilliant, characterised by a suspenseful narrative, which is typical of Madonna’s creativity in the studio. ‘This is the Future’ is crisp and rolling, an intelligent tool for every set. ‘Enveloping Times’ is punchy and hypnotic, an immense transcendental belter ready to be unleashed this summer. ‘Interfrequencies’ is an exhilarating rush to the head, as a killer bass synth and piston-like drums for a rave-ready finish.
title: Luigi Madonna - Italian Shocks - Drumcode - DC247

description:
https://drumcode.ffm.to/dc248

Breathe – the stunning eight-track mini album from long-standing British techno artist Mark Reeve out via Adam Beyer's iconic Drumcode Records.

Following a slew of critically acclaimed single and EP releases on Drumcode over the course of his esteemed decade-long career – the last of which came in the form of his mammoth Distance EP back in February 2020 – Breathe marks Mark Reeve's most extensive musical opus on the legendary imprint, and goes a long way in showcasing the inexhaustible creativity of one of the most prolific and original artists in techno today.

A career-defining moment for Reeve, Breathe has extraordinary allure and maintains the impressive quality of engaging the listener from the very start. A rich and complex body of work, the stunning eight-tracker goes far beyond Mark's trademark transcendental crowd pleasers, encompassing lilting moments of euphoric ambience alongside a sundry offering of full-throttle warehouse juggernauts and ravey breakbeat cuts.
title: Mark Reeve - Breathe - Drumcode - DC248

title: E-Dancer - Re:Generate - Drumcode - DC250

description:
https://drumcode.ffm.to/dc246

Bart Skils returns to Drumcode with a trio of dancefloor weapons. The artist has been one of the most consistent label contributors over the last 18 months, with two Truesoul EPs, a cut on A-Sides Vol.10 and now ‘New Era’, his second Drumcode EP in a year. ‘All Over My Body’ features a collaboration with well-regarded US producer/DJ/vocalist Superchumbo and is a ready-made festival track, propelled by a memorable vox hook, driving groove and thrilling effects. ‘Golden Temple’ is trademark Skils and builds to a hypnotic laser-kissed climax. ‘Dub Killer’ is punchy techno at its finest, capped off by a woozy vocal drop.
title: Bart Skils - New Era - Drumcode - DC246

description:
Against a Dark Background – the full-length studio album from long-standing British techno duo, Spektre – will be released in early 2020 on Pleasurekraft’s esteemed Kraftek imprint.

Following their critically-acclaimed debut album Casting Shadows Without Light in 2010 and their sophomore outing Cyclic Operations in 2013, Against a Dark Background will be the third studio long-player from partners Paul Maddox and Rich Wakley, who have been producing together under the Spektre moniker since 2006.

Currently in the top five-selling techno artists worldwide and with over 500,000 streams per month on Spotify, Spektre have taken the electronic music world by storm over the past few years, with their forward-thinking productions and high-intensity live performances resonating with legions of loyal techno fans across all corners of the globe.

Now key ambassadors for British dance music on a global level, Spektre’s chart-topping productions have received high praise from the likes of Adam Beyer, Carl Cox, Pleasurekraft and Alan Fitzpatrick and the duo are often hailed as one of the most exciting acts to emerge onto the UK techno scene over the past decade.

Talking about the forthcoming album, Spektre commented:

It had been over 5 years since the release of 'Cyclic Operations' when we first started work on the new album in earnest, so we wanted it to be a representation of how our music has evolved in that intervening period. The writing process itself was a lot more reductive than the previous two albums. We holed ourselves up for a few months and hammered out loads and loads of ideas, then filtered and refined the pool through playing them out and getting feedback from a few trusted pairs of ears, until "Against a Dark Background" began to crystallise into its final form.
title: Spektre - Against a Dark Background (Kraftek)

description:
This is the debut album of Swedish producer Daniel Andreasson, an artist that has both a sonically and artistic resemblance to the Skudge family of labels and artists.

Pushing his eighth year of releasing records, Andreasson has accomplished the task of creating a debut album that seem to tie together the sound of his previous EP's. Andreasson's sound is in line with a more outsider approach, but with a dance floor focus. A sound that he has been pushing since the beginning.

Artist: Daniel Andreasson
Title: LP1
Label: Skudge
Catno: SKUDGE-WLP03
Release Date: 29 September 2017

This approach shines through at the most on the tracks such as 'Mc35I# Rushup', 'Stay' and 'Dreams' as these specific tracks shows Andréassons more accomplished style. In between, the album keeps a perfect concept throughout. Taking breathers with its interludes and in general "shorter" tracks that hints of a ambient leaning urge to express himself, he never loses focus. A masterful debut album from a artist to keep your eye on!

description:
SKUDGE-W14
MONO JUNK
''Disillusions''

1 November Bass
2 Disillusions
3 Melody Boy's Melody


Hello! We are happy to announce this years first release!

Onto 2017, Skudge White returns with Finnish legend Mono Junk, who has been around since the early 90’s. Continuing in his own established tradition, he delivers three tracks that together spans 23 years.

First off on A1, a 14 minute journey takes us to the far depths of electronic music. Made in 2016, this beast of a track has all the true, vital ingredients of atmosphere: rolling and thundering beats and perfected synth work - one for the specialists!

Turning the 12” around, we find two pumpers from the archives. Dusted off in perfect harmony with the current musical state of affairs: Mono Junk, in collaboration with Pete Salone, showcases a true spirit and heartfelt blizzard of a tune, where ’Disillusions’ resembles the forgotten experimental touches of Techno’s early days.

’Melody Boy’s Melody’ goes into a sing-a-long (in the right way) appeal, with enchanting rhythms and a perfected melody, this is a heady piece with IDM resemblances.
title: MONO JUNK ''DISILLUSIONS'' (SKUDGE-W14)

description:
Often referred to as ‘The Pig’ and rarely spotted without shades, Mike ‘Aardvarck’ Kivits has remained a compelling figurehead within the Dutch underground for some two decades now, happily flitting between downtempo and high octane styles from release to release and generally sounding like no-one else out there. Now residing in the Indonesian paradise province of Bali, Kivits has developed a strong affiliation with the Skudge Records operation which commenced with his humongous remix of the Swedish act’s “Convolution” in 2010.
Having committed two full 12″ releases to the Skudge Presents cause, news now arrvies of a full Aardvarck long player on the label. Due for release in September, the cryptically-titled Co In Ci features eight new Aardvarck productions from Kivits and represents the ninth album the Dutch producer has released in the 13 years since his 2002 debut LP for Delsin, Find The Cow.
title: AARDVARCK ''CO-IN-CI'' (SKUDGE-PTLP01)

Max takes inspiration from Depeche Mode, as well as other artists such as Stevie Wonder, Pink Floyd, and Ricardo Villalobos. He also drew inspiration from rhythmic South American and Arabic music.
He started to play my music at school parties, for my own pleasure. In 2010, he tried to establish his label, but the project was postponed. Professionally engaged in DJ-ing from 2013 year. We present Color Of Crocus Canvas series .

A talented painter from Kherson /UA/ Konstantin Tereshchenko, inspired by the tracks of Kirik , provided his artistic work "Tears of Lust" for the cover this release !

Here are the words of the author of the picture :
October 31, 2014 , morning , while I was experiencing a very strong break with the "madame", it was very heavy ... And in my head was just  porn , really , all night !
And I was very surprised how it could even be combined ?!
And I decided to put this vision on canvas , as a result I had a picture:
"Tears of Lust":
Night morning . Thoughts lay on each other like insects , feeding on my magical energy. Stand before your eyes. The shadow scares the one who casts it. And rolling, rolling tears of lust ...

Konstantin Tereshchenko :
instagram.com/tereshenko_konstantin

"Coming from a recent position at #2 on the @Beatport Top 100 & receiving BBC Radio 1 national play… Jake joins Household Digital for our 110th Release. 
A special one which see’s a limited edition VINYL run in December 2021 of 110 records to accompany this milestone! (Keep an eye out on Bandcamp)

While the UK DJ/producer - Jake - is fairly new here, he provides 3 solid original tracks that caught the attention of various premiere channels, DJ's + artists who were eager to be onboard with this project.
The EP features remixes from two of the most renowned artists who are no strangers to the scene. 

‘Tech House’ originator - Terry Francis (Wiggle, Swag Records, Eukahouse) who needs little introduction, steps up and provides a solid chunky 9 minute rerub of the already dope original “Escalateher”. Adding twisted vocals from the illusive “Hive71” turning the track into something quite special. We would expect nothing less from the @fabric Resident DJ!

A more modern, yet quick rising producer - Joe Pompeo (SOUP, Cajual Records) provides the second remix to this body of work. Having collaborated with some of the worlds fastest growing names such as; Solardo, Sonny Fodera & Derrick Carter. He really shows why he is a force that is becoming more & more prevalent amongst the club scene in the U.S"

A long-standing name within the European electronic music landscape with over two decades of experience in the booth, Liège-based DJ and producer Jean-Yves Avarello, aka AAvA, continues to evolve as an artist. Making his production debut in 2012, he welcomed early support from artists such as Dubfire, Richie Hawtin, Roger Sanchez, DJ Sneak, and Nicole Moudaber, quickly establishing his presence as a producer within the worlds of house and techno. Next up for him, early June welcomes a debut outing on Butane’s renowned Little Helpers imprint as he reveals a seven-track mini-album project, showcasing his deep and diverse range as an artist.
 
“During 2020 my productions in lockdown spanned different styles I like, which is showcased across this EP for Little Helpers. I hope this ‘mini-album’ will make you travel through different styles and emotions as much as it does for me.” - AAvA
 
Combining a wealth of sounds and influences from across multiple genres, ‘Little Helpers 379’ sees a melting pot of styles from across the electronic world. From the slow-blooming, melodic opener’ Little Helpers 397-1’ to the eastern-influenced, groove-driven sounds of ‘Little Helper 379-2’ and ‘Little Helper 379-3’, AAvA’s skill for weaving rich and resonant melodies with crisp percussion patterns quickly becomes apparent.
 
‘Little Helpers 397-4’ ups the energy and delves deeper, utilising an ever-evolving web of organic percussion arrangements whilst introducing rich keys, subtle vocals, and sweeping synths throughout ‘Little Helpers 379-5’. To close ‘Little Helpers 379-6’ builds things up again as refined kicks and warped vocals float around murky low-ends, before rounding things out via the slinking, infectious tribal grooves of ‘Little Helper 379-7’.
title: AAvA - Little Helpers 379

This record has soundtracked some of our most cherished memories. From ecstatic club nights dripping with sweat to soft sunrises over serene Australian countryside. 


For many years 'Yotogi' a remained a rare dubplate, now it sees the light of day through Vessel records. The 12" contains three tracks and three sound skits that recreate the atmosphere in which it was produced - deep in the bowels of Osaka, Japan. A big arigatou to Shindo for allowing us to make it available, and to our friends in Japan for sharing their honest approach to house music culture. 

The full tracklist is as follows:

Love, Vessel.

description:
Norachi comes at you all slinky and smooth from the Victorian countryside with 4 tracks to rattle the bass bins of your deepest dancefloor. The optimist of the bunch; ‘Nurture’ reveals glimmering synths and tight percussion over a stout bassline, while the Reflective mix adds the tough yet melancholy attitude and robust mindset distinctive of Castlemaine streets in the year 2020.  
On the flip, Nature Bassline walks the line between beatdown and dub with hats lashing themselves over a bass melody reminiscent of classic Detroit works. The closer, Tool For Tim, is an exercise in after hours club moderation, settling itself into a dream loop you won’t wake up from.
Sleeve art by Gavin Fennessy.

description:
Taken from the new @limbotapes compilation "Shape Shifting Creatures Of Limbo " (LIMBO09). 
Buy tape/digital: https://limbotapes.bandcamp.com/album/shape-shifting-creatures-of-limbo

"It’s no secret that compilations are at the very core of the Limbo philosophy. This release reveals an extraordinary new project for the collection, in the form of dozen mutant remixes and versions of both back catalogue material and new amalgamations.

We welcome Om Unit to the label for the first time with a galloping dub mutation, Bristol’s slow-jam wizards OSVMVSM flip Limbo material in their signature woozy style and Limbo HQ rears its head in the form of Titus 12 and Dive Reflex Service both remixing and becoming the remixed.

Listeners will also behold powerful examples of work from the talented Eusebeia (one raucous breaks, one a stunning vocal performance), Rodney in trance dub mode, the expanding sounds of Universe All, and a dizzying rendition of MTF’s “Point Two” by Lupo | Coyote.

Joining the hybrid frenzy from overseas is past Bristol resident and all round dance floor killer Hartta, out of Seville, and recent label resident Caro, bringing their downtempo beats and vaporous sonics all the way from Sinixt territory in British Columbia, Canada.

All in all, this release is a vibrant package of quintessentially Limbo compounds. Sometimes menacing and energetic, other times reflective, tense or playful. The physical comes on hazardous yellow cassette with terrifyingly appropriate mutant fold out artwork, including your very own Limbo style cut-out mutant face-swap game... "

description:
Looks like all the storm is waving down recently and the rave times feel closer than ever...  so it's perfect timing to unleash the spanish rising star G.P.M with his first musical release ever!! 

Straight from Málaga (Spain), the young and talented producer has been around on the dancefloor attending loads of events and supporting the dnb scene in most of the aspects apart from creating the music itself; that was the moment to decide to dive into the drum & bass sound. 

The spark needed to download music making software appeared. He started to try and lay down some ideas. He quickly stepped into a couple electronic music schools to power up the knowledge curve then jumped into private mentoring by our sound guy Kursiva who has been supporting him from the very first moment. 

G.P.M has been working hard on the studio... 

With only 11 months of production experience he has just landed at South Yard’s headquarters with two tracks that caught our attention immediately because of their tightness and fresh sound.

Every Time is a track that hooked us from the first moment.  Reminding the Benny Page 2010’s vibes with those catchy and sweet Jamaican vocal bits twisted with 2021’s deep & gnarly basslines creating an old to the new combination that felt very refreshing at its first listen. 

The second song of the release is called Rolling Up and is a pure banger for the dance!! This track is a perfect example of the “less is more” fact and we love that!

Big amount of sub frequencies alongside the continuous resonant bass will hit your body. The straight 2-step drum pattern will get you jumping into the loop. This dj-friendly tune is the perfect pair for the main track and we are more than excited to drop this one on a big rig for all the massive & crew!

Follow G.P.M :
https://www.instagram.com/g.p.m_music/
https://soundcloud.com/user-62211443
tag_list: G.P.M "South Yard" "Every Time" "Rolling Up" DNB "Drum & Bass" Jungle
title: SY024 - G.P.M - Every Time

description:
La Phaze has been a long-standing fixture of the french scene, at the intersection of jungle, urban sound system beats and punk rock vibes (a combination style that they call 'Pungle'). After 20 years and 700 wild concerts all over the world, the band came back from a long hiatus and released the new album VISIBLE(S) in October 2020. The original duo (Damny writes the lyrics, both Arnaud and Damny work on the songwriting) has been joined in the meantime by the producer Speaker Louis. When the pandemic caused the band to cancel their tour, the 3 members of La Phaze focused their energy on their studio work and connected with some of the best artists from the reggae, jungle and drum & bass scenes. Joining forces with the hard working Spanish junglists of South Yard, the band is proud to deliver this 100% sound system EP.

With the distinctive vocal energy of Blackout JA  adding to Damny's lyrics and the production of Speaker Louis, this new version of their song 'One Way' is a dubwise dancefloor banger with a conscious message. La Phaze also welcomes the french jungle master Veak, who puts his touch on 'Highly Blessed' for a breakbeat-heavy filthy roller. Spanish reggae star Lasai, already present on the album, delivers here a special and extended version of the song 'Liberticide', in a classic 90s dancehall style. Having worked closely with Damny in the past, Barcelona-based dub specialist Chalart58 offers a brand new reggae cut of the tune 'Haute Sécurité'.

The real novelty of the EP is the title track 'Rebel', an original production which bridges the gap between the seminal La Phaze vibe and modern drum & bass. This tune showcases the band's return to a more digital and electronic sound, fully in touch with their history and with a forward-thinking attitude. Expect the trio to provide serious ammunition for your turntables, until they can finally ignite the dancefloors again with their live show! Pungle is Massive!
title: SY022 - La Phaze - Rebel EP

description:
South Yard is very glad to present its next release: Roll To The Old. 100% Iberian product.

At the controls, the well-known and prolific duo from Cordoba, Spain, Boombassbrothers.

Influenced by Reggae and Hip Hop, lovers of Drum & Bass, Jungle and Breaks, these brothers have been motivating the scene for years with their sessions and production having already edited a considerable amount of works with different national and international labels. It is a real pleasure for us to count with them in our ranks with their first South Yard Ep.

The main track, Roll To The Old, from which the Ep takes its name, stands out thanks to the catchy sample used in combination with a classic Amen Break and a thick and explosive bassline.
The second track, Bashment, is a collaboration with Bassflexx, another junglist jewel from Spain, straight outta the Bellota Dubs collective. 
The production features the vocals of rapper Jamalski, which perfectly suit this classic roller. The result of this collaboration promises to set the dancefloor on fire.

The junglist community is growing more and better every day and we are very proud to be a part of it.❤️💛💚
Hit  play, share, and support the scene.
[SP] 
Desde South Yard estamos muy contentos de anunciar nuestro siguiente release: Roll To The Old. Producto 100% ibérico.
A los mandos, el conocido y prolífico dúo cordobés Boombassbrothers.
Influenciados por el reggae y el hiphop, amantes del drum&bass, jungle y los breaks, estos hermanos llevan años motivando a la escena con sus sesiones y sus producciones, a sus espaldas ya llevan editados una cantidad considerable de trabajos con diferentes sellos nacionales e internacionales.
Para nosotros es un verdadero placer contar con ellos en nuestras filas y editarles su primer Ep en South Yard.
El tema principal, Roll To The Old, da nombre al Ep, y destaca por el pegadizo sampler utilizado en combinación con un amenbreak clásico y una gruesa y explosiva línea de bajo.
El segundo track , Bashment, es en colaboración con el extremeño Bassflexx, otra de las joyas del jungle español, perteneciente al colectivo Bellota Dubs. 
La producción cuenta con las vocales vocales del rapero Jamalski, que se adaptan perfectamente a este clásico roller.
El resultado de esta colaboración promete incendiar la pista de baile.
La comunidad junglist crece cada día más y mejor y estamos muy orgullosos de ser parte de ello.
Dale al play, comparte,y apoya a los artistas locales.

description:

Hybrid links Madrush MC to offer up “Better Surrender”, a bass-line driven, minimal roller with rich musical elements and dark vocals that reach out to the underground D & B skankers. The flip side sees Hybrid link with Liondub and the legend Navigator on a ’93 inspired “hardcore junglism” track for the old school heads.

description:
Liondub presents the 3rd single taken from DJ Hybrid’s forthcoming LP “Diary Of An Everyday Junglist”. Hybrid joins forces with the ever-talented Rider Shafique to offer up “Rougher Than Rough,” a brilliant roller that starts with emotive piano and pads, but then rises quickly with hard hitting 808 energy and a dark vocal warning from Rider about the perils of street life. On the drop, rolling modern drums kick in and are accentuated perfectly by Hybrid’s amen edits and modulated top bass drones. On the flip is the updated 2021 remix of “Shockin Out”, a stand out Jungle banger that released 3 years ago on Liondub’s Street Series.  
The full LP has been crafted by the Coventry based artist over 2 years, and features a legendary array of collaborators; it’s a massive undertaking that is both musically moving, and historically relevant as it marks the unity between two label heads and leaders in the UK & US Jungle Drum & Bass scene.

description:
LF RMX 023

A - Robert Armani - Hit Hard (Len Faki Hardspace Mix)
B - Musik Aus Strom - A2 Untitled (Len Faki Hardspace Mix)	

More unheard edits from Len Faki‘s personal vaults on this release, harking way back to the mid-'90s and their relentless, hard-hitting styles.
 
Chicago legend Robert Armani, also still hailed as one of the originators of hardstyle by many, makes an appearance on the A-side. And it‘s that characteristic, punishing kick sound, which is still present in the modern edit, carrying on the original‘s obtuse force albeit shrouded in a much more ominous and austere veil.
 
German IDM-duo Funkstörung well left their mark on the millennium’s last decade. Even with their side-project Musik Aus Strom that restricted itself to a series of forward-pointing, no-nonsense acid-techno albums. Len Faki picks out a track showcasing the raw and vital essence of that Acid Planet-time and molds it into a soaring, sizzling and well-balanced tool, tricky and perky at once. 

All proceeds of this record go to the charity project Straßenkinder e.V. in Berlin who act against child poverty and help steet children. 

Bandcamp: bit.ly/LFRMX023
www.straßenkinder-ev.de
www.lfrmx.com
tag_list: lfrmx "robert armani" "musik aus strom" "len faki" remixes edits charity techno rave Acid berlin Electronic
title: LF RMX 023 | Robert Armani, Musik Aus Strom

description:
LF RMX 020

A - Plastikman - Hypokondriak (Len Faki Hardspace Mix)
B - Tres Demented - Brainfreeze (Len Faki Hardspace Mix)

Celebrating its 20th release, this edition of LF RMX features appearances from two of the scene‘s cutting edge producers: Richie Hawtin under his guise of Plastikman alongside Carl Craig‘s Tres Demented-alias. 

While Hawtin‘s original might seem a minimalistic bleeping experiment to some, Len Faki‘s edit has plenty of groove to it. Equipped with substantial low-end frequency and a solid kick, the track slowly develops an ambiance that's spooky, tribal and mesmerizing.

The flip carries an equally strong rework, its grand acid riff and standout-vocals holding center stage, with newly added percussion driving the momentum that turn this one into a peak-time hitter in true crazed-out Tres Demented-style.

www.lfrmx.com
more info about the project here: strassenkinder-ev.de
tag_list: plastikman "tres demented" "len faki" "richie hawtin" "carl craig" remixes Techno lfrmx
title: LF RMX 020 - Plastikman | Tres Demented

description:
LF RMX 018

A Wishmountain - Radio (Len Faki Hardspace Mix)
B Wishmountain - Bottle (Len Faki Deepspace Mix)

When Len Faki tackles an old school Matthew Herbert record (released 1998 under his rare Wishmountain moniker), the outcome couldn‘t get any better. Granting the haunting ’Radio’ a proper kick to beat along the chugging, percussive craze of the original, it quickly turns into a mesmerizing trip down memory lane. On the flip Faki leads an excursion deep into the jungle, with ’Bottle’ sporting an atmosphere so immersive, it‘s easy to get lost in the underbrush of this one!

As with all releases of LF RMX, the proceeds of this record will be forwarded to the Berlin organization Straßenkinder e.V. to be used in actions against child poverty. 

www.lfrmx.com

description:
LF RMX 017

A1 Planet Love Ink - Living In Pain (Len Faki Deepspace Mix)
A2 Brotherhood Of Structure - We Are Structure (Len Faki Hardspace Mix)
B Illuminatae - Tremora Del Terra (Len Faki Hardspace Mix)

For this edition of the LFRMX-series Len Faki is turning to 1990‘s trance and acid. The bpm might be lower than back in the days, but there‘s just as much energy coming off these irresistible tunes in their updated versions.

Featuring the original‘s sizzling synth work by Kompakt co-founder Wolfgang Voigt‘s early collaborative projects, Planet Love Ink strikes an upbeat chord in order to show off its grand piano break for maximum effect.

Equally tapping into the early nineties, Structure – We are Structure is a weighty acid banger with no frills attached. Straight, honest and nailing era‘s vibe to the core. B-Side‘s all about old school trance, booming breaks, and epic synth-sweeps, in this instantly captivating, elevating and driving rework of Illuminatae – Tremora del Terra, a hymn to many back in the days.


As usual with LFRMX releases, the proceeds of this record will be forwarded entirely to charity organization Straßenkinder e.V., who are working to offer help to the children living on the streets of Berlin.

www.lfrmx.com

description:
FINALLY, it's got an official release! My little Sunrise Jungle rework I made of “foreigner - i want to know what love is”. Made for sunrises....

Out now on Spinnin Deep:
Stream / Download: found.ee/WannaKnow

This is a story about a little blonde girl’s journey about her love for going to a festival in the desert and playing sunrise sets’ Viv says. ‘This little girl discovered meditation along her journey and loved to be in the present moment because that’s where she learned true happiness is.

So she wanted to make a special edit to inspire happiness and positivity in people while they are dancing the sunrise away deep in the desert, truly being in the present moment. That moment is absolutely everything, there’s nothing like it. This special edit is of Foreigner - i want to know what love is.

Skankandbass is dedicated towards the official promotion of record labels and artists in the world of drum & bass music. Since inception in 2009, Skankandbass has unearthed some of the freshest talents in the scene and has opened many doors for unsigned artists. Now, through Skankandbass Introducing we release a series of free download singles which aims to spread the work of the best unsigned, newcomer artists who deserve more recognition.

S&B091 comes to us all the way from South Africa as we welcome Dopplershift to Skankandbass Introducing.  The budding Cape Town based talent is no stranger to our channel, having made numerous appearances via his excellent releases on Delta9, Four Corners, Hyperactivity, SINE and Monk Audio.  For SNB091 he recruits fellow SA producers Krispy and Real Feel’s on his powerful single ‘The Gallow / Diamonds In The Sky’.

description: Camo Tribe welcomes Temper Dee to the label with his debut 13 track album. Hailing from Norwich, UK, Temper Dee has been producing since around 2000, and had a track called "B-Line Hassle" played on 1 Xtra by L-Double & Crissy Criss, who said the track was very "Dillinja-esque"!!! Fast forward to 2021, Temper Dee released a massive EP Big & Heavy Recordings that shot up the charts in all the download stores. Having kept in close contact with Label boss Pablo G over the last 6 months, Temper Dee has gone from having a 4 track EP to a 13 track album of pure bangers, he is one to be watched and is going to have a massive future going forward!

description:
e·go·tism - noun - the practice of talking and thinking about oneself excessively because of an undue sense of self-importance.

Basically, this is Nayte the Hermit's (@nayteth) moment of self-awareness, and the eternal internal struggle of musicians, swinging between narcissism & self-loathing. Not to fuel this huge ego any more, but Nayte's songwriting and production reach a new peak in this EP on DESKPOP. You may have heard their feature on the compilation DESKPOP: Pink Version, in which Nayte contributes cute vocals to a track produced by Jellybear. Often it sounds like a self-duet when switching between well-crafted vocal filters, both hyping themself up and talking themself down. "EGOTISM I" is a fantastic debut EP and will be stuck in your head for ages.

stream/download ~ https://smarturl.it/NayteTheHermit-EGO1

check out their song on DESKPOP: Pink Version, track #6 ~ https://smarturl.it/DESKPOP-Pink

and check out their first mixtape released earlier this month ~ https://smarturl.it/ConvenienceStoreNTH

Jackapedia created this wonderful EP artwork!
Website/Portfolio ~ https://www.jackapedia.design
Twitter ~ https://twitter.com/Jackapedia_

Here to show us how digital fusion can be danced to, Shady Monk from Philadelphia & That Andy Guy from Alabama have prepared a mixtape with fresh new songs and remixes of their faves. "Digital fusion" is basically the genre that DESKPOP first became known for before dipping into hyperpop. It's like vgm (video game music) but relies less on nostalgic sounds and more on complex rhythms + genre blending of jazz/funk/dance. Some of the featured musicians are well known in the digital fusion scene, and some are from the hyperpop network! Everything sorta “fuses” together hehe

description:
Berlin-based hyperbolic IDM artist IXXF lost their body but not their voice. Their debut is a genre-bending music project that separates the artistic output from the individual's body — from the voice of a gendered and embodied Persona.

Trap and deconstructed club music blend in with bold pop anthems - and even fragments of emo punk, into an artificial but yet heartwarming sound.  To conquer the idea of the artist's voice as a primal extension of the  singer themselves, a direct link from their anatomy to the audience, IXXF  uses digital effects and voice manipulation to free the music from the restrictions of the artist's physical presence.

IXXF has numerous features by gender challenging artists on like Pussy Riot, Catnapp, Galen Tipton, Jinka, Lamb Kebab, Recovery Girl, Atlas Moe and more on their debut album. These collabs sound like a single, disembodied voice that represents the music with a maximum of authenticity.

IXXF is an inclusive musical journey and proves that an artist is not defined by their persona, but can  become their own vision through simultaneous impersonation by a  multitude of bodies in various (fluid) forms.

👥 1MF music video: https://youtu.be/oO_5NZRo8ZM

Friends to the end IXXF and Catnapp stomp onto the dancefloor as the best dressed pair in the club, yelling over the microphone on this song about digital friendships. Best described as hyperpunk, the beat carrying "1MF" takes a sauntering pace, comfortably supporting the energetic vocals by booming and crashing methodically. Bearing their teeth on the cover art, IXXF and Catnapp are eager to scare away the fake friends accumulated through social media. Take a look at the music video where the two taunt their following on an Instagram Live stream, with both clothing and CGI flourishes designed by Ksti Hu.

💥 Everything Sucks music video: https://youtu.be/KJKHN4bIlik

CGI music video created by Ksti Hu for IXXF’s debut single, “Everything Sucks” portrays a character who feels helpless in a broken world. While crawling through the mud, IXXF wails “I SUCK AT THIS!” But as the camera pans around to abandoned commercial and material artifacts, one can only question if the character’s insecurities come as a product of their environment. Originally to be titled “I SUCK” we decided to change the title to “Everything Sucks” to tell those experiencing 2020 they can only be responsible for so much. There are tons of folks who internalize the bad and feel at fault or guilty. Hopefully this video reminds those people to look around to see we are all in this together. You don’t suck; Everything Sucks.

1MF Review from The Ransom Note:
https://www.theransomnote.com/music/news/ixxf-collaborates-with-catnapp-on-video-ahead-of-debut-album/

description:
"The main inspiration for the album is the idea that life is this big, long confusing footpath with a tonne of different offshoots. The only way you can get to see the entirety of what the footpath has to offer is to get lost from time to time, and to explore all these different, off-the-beaten-path trails. It can be kinda terrifying, sometimes it can feel like you’re never going to get back onto the main path, but ultimately you can’t truly experience what the world can be unless you actively try to discover it." - Former Hero
